  ## How to Create a Tag for a GitHub Release 

  1. From the master branch create the tag
     * `git tag -a tag_name`
  2. Add a message about the tag when prompted
     * Have the message match the title of the release
  3. Push up the tag
     * `git push origin tag_name`
  4. In GitHub navigate to the _releases_ tab, next to the _branches_ tag
  5. Select the _Tags_ button
  6. Click the group of three dots in the right corner
  7. Select _Create a Release_ 
